fields.name: Zamioculcas
fields.description:
He is the ideal room friend that you hardly have to worry about. 
In terms of sunlight, it has few requirements and requires very little water. 
Due to its fairly slow growth, the Zamioculcas is not particularly good at purifying the air. 
It is also slightly poisonous. 
Well, you can't have everything. 
Fortunately, he is so relaxed that he can handle this very well himself.

Pot: 21cm diameter
Height: 75cm with pot

fields.name: Calathea Medallion
fields.description:
She comes from Brazil. 
Due to its large leaves, it is an expert in purifying the air and it is also not poisonous. 
She likes the sun, but also likes the shade. 
She feels most comfortable with a little bit of both. 
Her most beautiful feature is her closing foliage at sunset and in the morning when the sun rises she welcomes all your love again with open leaves!

Pot: 19cm diameter
Height: 70cm with pot

fields.name: Beaucarnea
fields.description:
This Beaucarnea, also popularly called Elephant's Foot, is originally from Mexico and is an easy houseplant. 
This amigo belongs to the palm family and just like a camel, this green friend stores water in its trunk, so it can go without water for quite a long time. 
He likes a nice, light place. 
Even a place in direct sunlight is not a problem, but let him get used to this, otherwise his leaves will burn!
Pot: 21cm diameter. Height: 80cm with pot.

fields.name: Areca
fields.description:
Areca is native to Africa. 
It needs a lot of indirect light and water to really do it justice. 
He gives you delicious fresh purified air for the attention you give him. 
This is because it is especially good at removing the harmful substances formaldehyde, benzene, trichlorethylene and toluene from the air. 
The care therefore requires some attention, but you get so much in return!

Pot: 24cm diameter
Height: 130cm with pot

fields.name: Dracaena Marginata
fields.description:
The Dracaena Marginata is nice and easy going. 
He does not drink much and does not have to stand in the sun much, which is nice with our Dutch climate. 
He is not very handy with pets. 
We think that's because it's slightly poisonous. 
Furthermore, he is a very relaxed guy. 
He is also very good at purifying harmful substances from the air, such as benzene. 

Pot: 21cm diameter
Height: 100cm with pot

fields.name: Calathea Rufibarba
fields.description:
The Calathea Rufibarba has one of the most special qualities there is, and we are of course talking about closing her leaves when the sun has set. 
Officially she is a Calathea Rufibarba, but she falls asleep like a baby. 
Due to the size of its leaves, it is also an excellence in purifying the air. 
So she is a plant with a story and a skill! 

Pot: 19cm diameter
Height: 85cm with pot

fields.name: Ficus Lyrata
fields.description:
The Ficus Lyrata, to which she belongs, has been around for decades and is one of the most popular indoor plants on the market. 
The strength of the Ficus family lies in the enormous variety of subspecies that exist. 
From small to large, with round or heart-shaped leaves and from stately and classic to trendy and hip, nothing that the Ficus is not. 
She belongs to the trendy and hip Ficus who purify the air and are slightly poisonous. 
For a little love, she returns a lot of love. 

Pot: 21cm diameter
Height: 90cm with pot

fields.name: Phlebodium
fields.description:
In addition to its special leaves, this Phlebodium is also a great air purifier and therefore a very healthy housemate to have. 
In the Netherlands she is better known as the 'Blauwvaren'. 
She is quite thirsty, but does not need direct sunlight. 
Phlebodium, we love you!

Pot: 12cm diameter
Height: 35cm with pot

fields.name: Polyscias Fabian
fields.description:
This jungle-like Polyscias loves partial shade and requires a little more attention than your average room friend. 
He does not like to be in a draft, does not like it at all in the dark, but neither does direct sunlight. 
Like all members of the Plantsome family, he converts carbon dioxide into oxygen, which purifies the air in your room. 
Some plants can also filter other harmful substances such as benzene from the air, but this does not apply to him. 
By the way, heis a 'Polyscias' which is Greek and means 'much shade'. 
This refers to the fact that this plant offers a lot of shade.

fields.name: Pilea Depressa
fields.description:
She is related to the well-known pancake plant, but prefers the term 'crepe family' herself. 
She may think a bit highly of herself. 
That could have something to do with the fact that she likes to live in a hanging pot ...

Pot: 12cm diameter
Height: 21cm with pot

fields.name: Calathea Triostar
fields.description:
She is a Calathea Triostar. 
Her beautiful green with creamy-white pink leaves fit her personality perfectly, because she is very colorful and a bit alternative. 
She's actually quite a hippie. 
Do not be fooled by her sweet appearance because she likes to protest against war every day and smokes the necessary green cigarettes! 
"Make love not war," she said.

Pot: 19cm diameter
Height: 70cm with pot

fields.name: Yucca
fields.description:
Just do it, you'll be crazy enough. 
He is just a nice and easy houseplant that does not have too many requirements. 
He drinks very little and does not need any food. 
If you put it in a sunny spot, it will do best. 
Be careful with pets, dear Yucca is poisonous!
Pot: 27cm diameter. Height: 160cm with pot.

fields.name: Cactus Euphorbia
fields.description:
The Cactus Euphorbia hardly drinks anything and you can always count on him. 
In recent years it has become increasingly popular in Dutch living rooms. 
This is of course because it is wonderfully easy to care for and looks super tough. 
Mind you, approach him carefully. 
He is sometimes a bit irritable!

Pot: 21cm diameter
Height: 100cm with pot

fields.name: Ficus Exotica
fields.description:
The Ficus Exotica is not only provides a natural atmosphere, but also a healthy working and living environment. 
NASA has included the Ficus in the top 10 of most air-purifying plants in the world. 
The Ficus is even in it twice, because it is not only an air-purifying plant, but it also converts CO2 into oxygen, which ensures better air quality. 
What a hero!

Pot: 21cm diameter
Height: 100cm with pot

fields.name: Caryota Mitis
fields.description:
You can of course buy a 'normal' houseplant, but you can also go for our special owner Caryota Mitis. Why? 
Okay, here's the situation: You get your aunt to drink and she sees him standing there. 
Then she says this: 'Gosh, what a funny plant you have. Where did he buy that? '. 
And you say: 'Nice huh! I bought from Home Jungle. 
That's a nice plant webshop where you can buy plants. 
' Well, and then you know that you have bought a very nice houseplant.

fields.name: Philodendron Scandens
fields.description:
The Philodendron Scandens prefers to just take a dip in the sea, but at home you can only give her some water. 
This amigo thinks that her long leaves are tentacles and that she belongs near a pineapple deep in the sea ... okay then! 
Don't blame her, this Philodendron is thousands of years old and sometimes a stitch gets loose. 
Fortunately, she can continue for years, as long as she gets enough water and is not in direct sunlight!

Pot: 15cm diameter. Height: 20cm with pot.

fields.name: Monstera Deliciosa
fields.description:
This plant is a pro at purifying the air, but he's also a bit poisonous. So be careful with your pets!

Origin: Mexico
Width: pot is 21 cm in diameter
Height: with pot 60 cm 
Light: maximum 2 meters from a window

fields.name: Dracaena Lemon Lime
fields.description:
The Dracaena Lemon Lime is nice and easy to care for. 
He can take a beating and is not thirsty. 
He is happy with a little shade and is an absolute master at purifying the air. 
Substances such as benzene are nowhere safe from him. 
He seeks out those harmful substances, grabs them, never let go and filters the shit out of them. 

Pot: 21cm diameter
Height: 95cm with pot

fields.name: Strelitzia nicolai
fields.description:
Strelitzia nicolai is quite thirsty and needs a lot of sunlight. 
In the summer months he needs some plant food once every 2 weeks. 
Its beautiful large leaves make it an air-purifying plant, but what makes it especially special is of course its jungle look. 
Just look at him. What a beauty!

Pot: 19cm in diameter
Height: 80cm with pot
